doc.after: Phoenix is served by Phoenix Sky Harbor International Airport (IATA: PHX,Â ICAO: KPHX), one of the ten busiest airports in the United States, serving over 110,000 people on over 1000 flights per day.[267] The airport is centrally located in the metro area near several major freeway interchanges east of downtown Phoenix.
